race.comment: COCO DE LUXE (9) slick debut winner when she drifted back and launched late as fav from the wide gate when scoring over 1100m at Echuca. Can race closer from the low draw and take holding out in this average C1. FAERIE (5) snagged back from the gate and chipped away late when sixth over 1000m at Cranbourne. Winning rider hops back on, and the map looks much kinder today.  GURU TWO (2) fitter after two runs back and will find this easier. Jumped in trip with the 59.5kg when a fading sixth over 1300m at Wodonga. Tongue-tie goes on and ready to deliver. WOLF ISLAND (8) has not raced since scoring over 1300m at Canberra on October 10. Include.
